physical_examinations.vital_signs: Normal vital signs and oxygen saturation.
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Abdomen was soft without distention, with tenderness in the right upper quadrant; spleen tip palpable; matted, firm lymph nodes in the inguinal region; hyperpigmented scaly plaques on the lower legs and waist; normal remainder of the examination.

White-cell count was 5800 per cubic millimeter, with 73% neutrophils, 14% lymphocytes, 6% monocytes, and 7% eosinophils; C-reactive protein was 9.7 mg per liter; angiotensin-converting enzyme level was 55 U per liter; ECG showed normal sinus rhythm with borderline early-repolarization abnormality and T-wave inversions in leads V1 and V2.
